fields.title: patch katsu data model for high-priority fields
fields.summary: Based on the data coverage spreadsheet, identify high-priority fields - those that exist in more than one cohort - that cannot be ingested into katsu.
fields.content:
Projects
CanDIG
DIG-873

DIG-894

patch katsu data model for high-priority fields



Description

Based on the data coverage spreadsheet, identify high-priority fields - those that exist in more than one cohort - that cannot be ingested into katsu. 

Depending on the number of fields, we may want to further prioritize based on user-defined importance. 

Then, patch the katsu data model / ingest to capture the highest-priority fields. This may include adding fields to extra-properties where they do not fit into the current mcode schema. 

This is the (unprioritized) list of MoH fields that fit the criteria, based on year 1 PM2C and POG cohorts. We have raw data, but cannot ingest into the current katsu model:

fields.title: Configure AWS CLI on an EC2 Instance
fields.summary: Open terminal and type the following curl command. This can be found in AWS Site : curl “https://awscli.amazonaws.com/AWSCLIV2.pkg" [sudo installer -pkg AWSCLIV2.pkg -target /
fields.content: First create a key pair. Key pair consist of a public and private key, that is used to ssh [or connect] to EC2 instance. Use this command and make sure you change “MyKeyPair” to your key pair name: aws ec2 create-key-pair — key-name MyKeyPair — query ‘KeyMaterial’ — output text > MyKeyPair.pem
